During winter, the wind removes "makeup" from the vibrant Hengshui Lake. More than 20,000 tundra bean geese travel long distances to spend the season here. Click on the video to learn more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Hebei series Hebei Province hosts the largest forest park in northern China, Saihanba National Forest Park, and the country's largest expanse of coastal sand dunes, the Golden Coast National Nature Reserve. Here, you will find unique landforms and a rich variety of plants and animals. For more: Hebei series | Episode 1: Beautiful Highland Hebei series | Episode 2: Boundary River Hebei series | Episode 3: Wetland in the Snow Hebei series | Episode 4: The Rhythm of Winter Hebei series | Episode 5: Golden Coast Hebei series | Episode 6: Qilihai Hebei series | Episode 7: Wetland on the Plain Hebei series | Episode 8: Forever Home (Cover image CFP) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)